						<p>To be fair, when I wrote that we must take care not to become the bankers, I wasn't speaking politically. If you read the article in context, you'll see I'm making a technical reference to the fact that our current system is comprised more of patches than actual stuff any more and that while Bitcoin is fresh new and simple, it could some day become that too.</p>
<p>Just as the founders of the U.S. gave us the tools to someday overthrow a regime just like the regime they overthrew in the form of the constitution, we must ensure that we are watchful and replace systems as they need replacing, not after they've been in decline for decades.</p>
